Merged from ticket 22280748  
      Subject: Issue with Freestyle Libre Sensor 2 - Request for Replacement or Refund  
      Description:  
 Dear PharmEasy Customer Care Team, 
   
 Hope you're doing well. 
   
 I've reached out to you regarding a concerning issue with my Freestyle Libre Sensor 2 glucose monitor, which I purchased from PharmEasy on 5th December 2025 - Product received on 8th December. The sensor was supposed to work for 14 days after placement on my arm, but it stopped working after just 4 days. The sensor displayed a message saying, "For safety reasons, your sensor has stopped working." 
   
 I’m extremely disappointed and dissatisfied with this experience, especially considering I paid ₹4,450 for a sensor with a 14-day lifespan. With it stopping after just 4 days, I feel my money has gone to waste. 
   
 I request you to kindly look into this matter urgently and help me with either a replacement sensor or a full refund. I’ve attached the order details and sensor information below for reference. 
   
 
   - *Order ID:*  655929357294141440
   
 
 - *Product:* Freestyle Libre Sensor 2 
 - *Purchase Date:* 5 December 2025 
   
 I appreciate your prompt attention to this issue. Looking forward to a swift resolution. 
   
 Thank you for your help. 
   
 Best regards, 
 Jaideep Singh

notes.body: Hello Tejas,     Greetings from PharmEasy!  With regards to your order #658493242171568128-84728, I see a return request has already raised for the damaged VYMADA 50MG STRIP OF 14 TABLETS quantity of 1. I am sorry to know that you have received medicines in a damaged condition.  As per the records, the medicine was picked up on today. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund amount of Rs. 556.70 will be processed and initiated within 48 hours. Also, once the refund is initiated, it will reflect in your bank account in 5 to 7 business days.    I appreciate your patience in the meantime.     For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the Need Help section. Alternatively, you can also call us on 08071324888.   Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay healthy!   Regards,  Habiba
notes.body_html:
Hello Tejas,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regards to your order #658493242171568128-84728, I see a return request has already raised for the damaged VYMADA 50MG STRIP OF 14 TABLETS quantity of 1. I am sorry to know that you have received medicines in a damaged condition.

As per the records, the medicine was picked up on today. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund amount of Rs. 556.70 will be processed and initiated within 48 hours. Also, once the refund is initiated, it will reflect in your bank account in 5 to 7 business days.

I appreciate your patience in the meantime.

For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the Need Help section. Alternatively, you can also call us on 08071324888.

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay healthy!

Regards,
Habiba

notes.body: Hello Rana,      Greetings from PharmEasy!     This email is with regards to your order #657248377607983104-93971, We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.     As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the COTARYL SQUAT JAR OF 75GM CREAM  on 15th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.     Please note that the medicine will be collected within 48 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 5 business days. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source account within 7-10 business days.     We appreciate your patience in the meantime.     We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.     Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,  PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Rana,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with regards to your order #657248377607983104-93971, We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of the COTARYL SQUAT JAR OF 75GM CREAM  on 15th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.
 
Please note that the medicine will be collected within 48 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 5 business days. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source account within 7-10 business days.
 
We appreciate your patience in the meantime.
 
We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy

helpdesk_ticket.description:
I am submitting this grievance regarding the repeated negligence and
unacceptable service experienced with my medicine order (Order ID:
656317517474824192).

Summary of Events:

On 10th December, the delivery agent asked me to come to Bihpur Chowk
(approx. 3 km from my residence) to collect the medicines. I refused, and
he assured delivery on 11th December.

The order was not delivered on 11th December.

I contacted Customer Support on 11th December, and a complaint was
registered.

On 12th December, I again contacted Customer Support. I was assured of
escalation, but no callback was received from any senior executive till
date.

Despite receiving an “Out for Delivery” message, the order was still not
delivered.

Due to continuous delay and the deteriorating health of my parents, I
personally contacted your courier partner’s office and collected the
medicines myself.

Later, PharmEasy falsely marked the order as “Delivered on 13th December”
and closed the ticket as “Resolved,” which is factually incorrect and
misleading.


Concerns:

This was a medicine order, not general merchandise.

There was zero accountability, repeated generic responses, and no proper
communication.

Senior support never contacted me despite assurances.

Claiming delivery by PharmEasy when the customer had to collect the
medicines himself is misrepresentation.


This behaviour is completely unacceptable and reflects gross negligence in
handling essential healthcare services.

Additional Requests:

1. Please provide the process for permanent deletion of my PharmEasy
account, as I no longer wish to continue with your services.


2. For any future communication related to this grievance, call only on the
registered account number linked with my ID, and not on the delivery
address contact number.



I expect this grievance to be taken seriously and addressed with
accountability.

Regards,
Keshav Deo
Mob:- 9113468578
